UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2123
1 AN ACT relating to solid waste management service companies.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 109.045 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) As used in this section, "confidential business information" means the following
5 information relating to[ privately] contracted solid waste management services[ that
6 are not being provided pursuant to a franchise agreement]:
7 (a) Commercial or residential customer service prices;[ or]
8 (b) Commercial or residential customer lists; and
9 (c) Any other proprietary or sensitive business information of a service
10 company or its customers.
11 (2) Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, unless by order of a court of
12 competent jurisdiction, a county or waste management district, or any of its agents,
13 officials,[ or] employees, contractors, consultants, or other persons acting on its
14 behalf or for its benefit, shall not compel the production or submission of, or
15 otherwise request, acquire, receive, review, or possess confidential business
16 information from a service company or its customers by any means, including but
17 not limited to requests made to other public agencies that may cause the release
18 of confidential business information[to any county or waste management district].
19 (3) Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, confidential business
20 information shall be exempt from disclosure under the requirements of KRS
21 61.870 to 61.884.
22 (4) If any confidential business information is obtained in violation of this section,
23 the county or waste management district shall:
24 (a) Immediately secure the information to prevent further access or
25 dissemination;
26 (b) Require the return or certified destruction of the confidential business
27 information; and
